fighting something while other people are attacking, youve been tanking the whole fight and FD and succeed... but the mob doesnt care that you seem dead and continues to beat on you... (normally happens in karnors a lot)<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
This is near the top of the list on most annoying bugs for me.  Hard as hell to FD anything off when other people are on the hate list.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> 7. This one happens in FV occasionally. You'll aggro a spider<br>
or drolvarg and run to town and they won't follow. Then<br>
when you finish banking you'll casually leave town towards<br>
FM or DL only to have the entire spider or drolvarg<br>
population converge onto you when you get far enough<br>
out (this only works if they are blue to red con).<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
This isn't a bug.<br>
<br>
You piss off some monster.  You outrun him.  He, in a fit of rage, runs back to all of his pals.  &quot;This n00b outran me, let's get him next time we see him.&quot;  &quot;Yeah!&quot;<br>
<br>
In more specific terms, the Kunark expansion brought a new feature, both good and bad.  The good was, if you got far enough ahead of a mob, he'd stop chasing you (old world mobs will still chase you all across the zone).  The bad was, you remain on his hate list until he's killed or you zone/log/die, and his hate list will transfer to every assisting mob he passes.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> &quot;spell recovery time not yet met&quot;<br>
<br>
<br>
ah yeah who doesnt just LOVE this one? since it only happens on HEALING SPELLS!?!?!?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Actually, this is a bug that happens to all casters.  It just happens only on spells with short casting times.  Huge bane to healers and Enchanters.  It's gotten me killed before, trying to fire off one more stun, barely hanging on .. &quot;Spell recovery time not yet met.&quot;<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> oh, and amen to the buffless zoning bug. verant states it's a death-save which is BULL.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Personally, it's saved me more than it's been a nuisance.  Zoning low on health when you're dotted (clears DoTs too, iirc), trying to escape a train, etc, it's been worth having to recast buff.  I'd definitely agree that it's a death-save.<br>
<br>
